  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n\r\n## Problem \r\n\r\nSometimes, in about 1 case out of 7, an error appears on the login that the wrong password was entered (although the password is 100% correct). When trying again after receiving an error, the login is sometimes successful, but sometimes the app crashes.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"326\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-04-14 at 12 06 02\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/67952253/232015539-2284d0a2-7c9a-409a-82f6-ff06442d7101.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\nAlso sometimes this error occurs with the same conditions:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"325\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-04-14 at 12 06 36\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/67952253/232015692-19688f97-89ad-4b78-b0b3-ee5e13ae7cfe.png\">\r\n\r\nIt is important to note that the problem is only reproducible on a _specific Wi-Fi_ (the same one that has issues with receiving messages). The case was also tested in two other locations with a connection to other Wi-Fi, as well as in the same location, but on the mobile network.\r\n\r\nLogs with the error and crash:\r\n\r\n[wrongpassword1.log](https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/files/11231602/wrongpassword1.log)\r\n\r\nFor me, the issue is currently reproducible only on Android devices.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nCan log in even with an interrupted connection\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nError and crash\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1. Create an account \r\n2. Log out > Log in several times till you get the `Oops, wrong password` error\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: nightly 14/04\r\n- Operating System: Android\r\n\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Please, add logs/notes if necessary)\r\n\r\n",
